article.headline: Robert Morris 104, Wagner 56
article.story: MOON TOWNSHIP, Pa. -- Rob Robinson scored 20 points and six players scored in double figures as Robert Morris won its sixth straight game, defeating Wagner 104-56 Saturday night. Jeremy Chappell scored 17 points, Gary Wallace 15, Jimmy Langhurst 14, Dallas Green 13 and Khalif Foster 10 for Robert Morris (12-7, 7-1 Northeast Conference). Llewchean Radford scored 14 points and Joey Mundweiler and Jamal Smith each added 11 for Wagner (10-7, 3-4). The Colonials outscored Wagner 34-12 in the paint and converted 22 turnovers into 29 points. Wagner shot 31.5 percent (17-for-54) in the game while Robert Morris shot 40-for-66 (60.6 percent).
